{{see|Crystal}}
==English==

===Pronunciation===
*krĭsʹtəl, /ˈkrɪstəl/, /<tt>"krIst@l</tt>/

*{{audio|En-ca-crystal.ogg|Audio (CA)}}

===Etymology===

From Old English ''cristal'' (clear ice, clear mineral), from Old French ''cristal'', from Latin ''crystallum'' (crystal, ice), from Ancient Greek ''krystallos'' (ice), from ''kryos'' (frost); from the Proto-Indo-European base ''*kru(s)-'', meaning ''hard, hard outer surface''. <br>{{etystub}}Needs Greek script, not just a transliteration. [[Arabic]] "قريس (QRYS, qarees) or قريت(QRYT, qareet)" from [[Sanskrit]].

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun-reg-both}}

# {{countable}} An [[array]] of [[atom]]s (mineral or otherwise) possessing [[long-range]] [[order]].
# {{countable}} A piece of glimmering, shining [[mineral]] resembling [[ice]] or [[glass]].
# {{uncountable}} A fine type of [[glassware]], or the material used to make it.

